cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.CL. 

The paper proposes a meta-learning algorithm for few-shot learning in image classification tasks. The algorithm utilizes a linear transformer that carries out null-space projection of neural network outputs. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also involves neural networks, which suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with classification tasks, which could also place it in the sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language).
